'''Runite rocks''' are the second-highest level rock in ''[[Old School RuneScape]]'', bested by [[amethyst crystals]], requiring 85 [[Mining]] to mine. When successfully mined, the player receives a [[runite ore]] and 125 Mining [[experience]]. After being mined, runite rocks take 12 minutes to [[respawn]]. They are highly popular and often are depleted of their resources, which prompts players to [[switch worlds]] to find rocks that haven't been mined. It is recommended not to hop to busy servers as busy worlds are more likely to have their [[ores]] already depleted. 

Mining runite ore is not recommended for players who are solely interested in leveling their mining skill due to how slowly the rocks are successfully mined. For example, to level from 98 to level 99, most players will need to spend at least 139814 mining attempts to gather enough to runite. This amounts to roughly 3 days of continuous mining. 

When mining runite, players may find it useful to keep track of the time that they mined the ore as well as the world number. If done accurately, players can hop to other worlds (keeping more such notes along the way) to mine runite while keeping an eye on the time, and then hop back to worlds where they previously mined runite when it is about time for the ore to respawn. This method of collecting runite ore does not need to be used when mining outside of popular [[member]] areas, such as the [[Fossil Island|Fossil Island mine]] requiring [[Bone Voyage|Bone voyage]] to access said mine, or at secluded areas like the [[Central Fremennik Isles mine]], which requires starting [[The Fremennik Isles]]. Moreover, starting [[Mourning's End Part II]] and wearing [[Mourner gear]] opens up the [[Mourner Tunnels mine]], which is another remote mine for members.[[File:Lava_Maze_Rune_Mine.png|thumb|250x250px|[[Lava Maze Rune Mine]] is currently the only place for [[free-to-play]] [[Runite ore|rune]] miners.]]Runite rocks in places like the [[Central Fremennik Isles mine]] are commonly targeted by players, and as such, there is more need to worry about the ore being contested, whereas the popular [[Lava Maze runite mine]] among [[free player]]s is almost always taken. Member worlds are more empty. However, such places in the [[Wilderness]] are usually dangerous due to high-level [[monsters]] and, more importantly, [[player killers]]. The amount of players and especially bots change every few hours and some mines are better at certain hours.

Wearing either [[superior mining gloves]] or [[expert mining gloves]] while mining a runite rock grants a 12.5% chance for the rock to not deplete upon mining a runite ore, allowing you to mine an additional ore before depleting.

